2004-09-29 08:36  twoodall

	* src/path/: common/BaseDesc.h, gm/header.h, gm/init.cc,
	  gm/path.cc, gm/recvFrag.cc: - change BaseAck to pass along send
	  sequence number - so that we can verify   the send fragment is
	  pointing to the correct send descriptor. In the case	 of
	  duplicate transmissions/acks - the ack could be pointing to a
	  send fragment   that has been reused.  - change gm init code to
	  force the number of recv tokens to not exceed the   number of
	  send tokens. Otherwise, w/ reliability enabled, or when using
	  sync sends, we can easily overrun the ability to generate
	  ackowledgments,   as each recv token requires a send token for
	  the ack.

